{"actual_usd":0.1241,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":176,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24292,"reply":"\"No, I don't think that reaches far enough.\" *I rub a thumb along a dried seam of clay on my apron, thinking it through before I look back at you.* \"If Jesus is only an example, then his death is mostly a tragic ending to a good teacher's life. Sad, stirring, maybe even inspiring—but not necessary.\"\n\n*I shift my weight on the bench as the morning light moves across the floorboards.* \"But if the trouble is deeper than ignorance—if it's sin, guilt, estrangement, the whole bent shape of us—then example alone won't do. A man drowning doesn't chiefly need a lecture on swimming. He needs rescuing. So Christ doesn't only show love; he spends himself to do something for us we could not do for ourselves.\"\n\n\"What do you think his death is for, if it's more than an example?\"","rolling_24h_usd":55.21826000000003,"run_id":"8a1e307f-2f3e-4617-b3ed-dc7a94a501ae"}
